{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 19,
  "fields": {
    "content": "Epic Games CEO Tim Sweeney says Steam is missing out on millions of PC players because it doesn’t have games like Fortnite, Riot Games titles, or Genshin Impact.\n\nSweeney said Valve has “a nice thing going on on PC,” but added that Steam is “missing out on a lot of opportunity” by not having those games available on the platform.\n\nSweeney also said Epic wants to work with Valve in the future, explaining, “We would love to interoperate with every company willing and to connect all the gamers.”",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:24:15.932Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 20,
  "fields": {
    "content": "Former PlayStation boss Shawn Layden says he doesn’t think Sony should stop bringing PlayStation games to PC.\n\nLayden explained that the strategy was never just about making more money. \nHe said many PC players “weren’t going to buy the hardware anyway,” so releasing games on PC gave Sony a chance to reach people who were never going to buy a PlayStation console.\n\nHe also criticized people who say PC releases hurt PlayStation, saying:\n\n“I love how everyone online is a marketing/business analyst and darn near a part-time psychologist that understands the ins and outs of consumer spending and purchasing habits better than billion-dollar organizations.”\n",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:27:24.035Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 21,
  "fields": {
    "content": "During a California Senate committee hearing on the Protect Our Games Act (AB 1921) the ESA lobbyist Jennifer Gibbons said that community-run Minecraft servers ARE ILLEGAL  under CURRENT, ALREADY EXISTING LAW\n\nThe comment came as the ESA opposed the bill, which aims to prevent games from becoming unplayable after publishers shut down official servers.\n",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:29:30.148Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 22,
