    "content": "According to Variety, Netflix is developing a live-action TV series based on the Persona game franchise.\n\nThe series will be produced by 21 Laps, the studio behind Stranger Things. SEGA’s Toru Nakahara is also attached as an executive producer.\n\nLet's see how Netflix ruins this.",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:30:10.070Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 23,
  "fields": {
    "content": "An Apple Watch Ultra was badly damaged after its owner crashed a motorcycle while trying to avoid a car, but the owner believes the watch protected the arm from a much worse injury.\n\nThe owner said, “My chunky titanium AWU took direct and full impact of my fall, which thankfully saved my arm from full contact to the pavement.”\n",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:32:56.617Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 24,
  "fields": {
    "content": "These Apple Watches can be lifesavers. From being able to ping your phone when you lose it, fall detection if you take a nasty fall, or being able to detect erratic and irregular heart beats\n",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:33:18.022Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 25,
  "fields": {
    "content": "The upcoming Metroidvania SHADE Protocol has already reached more than 150,000 Steam wishlists and 10,000 Steam followers. \n\nThe studio called the campaign “life-changing for our team.”\n\nThe Kickstarter campaign has raised over $275,000, far surpassing its original $40,000 funding goal.\n\n“We hit 150K+ wishlists, 10K followers on Steam, and surpassed $230K on Kickstarter all in the same day… and THEN Emi Evans, vocalist for NieR Automata and Dark Souls amongst many other games, shares that she’s a stretch goal for our game. Don’t wake me up please!”",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:34:21.107Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 26,
  "fields": {
    "content": "George Broussard  says he has heard from an internal source that Xbox could close several studios and will be like “the meteor that took out the dinosaurs.”\n\nHe isn’t sharing the names but says the information came from someone inside the company.\n\nBroussard said that if the information is true, it could be the biggest round of layoffs the gaming industry has ever seen. He also claims that even the studios that stay open will face layoffs.\n\n“If it’s even close to true (and it’s from inside), this will likely be the largest single layoff event in gaming history.”\n\n“Xbox is going to be supremely unpopular for a very long time, and the devastation is going to reverberate like the meteor that took out the dinosaurs.”",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T13:35:11.502Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
