  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 67,
  "fields": {
    "content": "Capcom has opened up about how difficult Pragmata’s early development really was,\nDirector Cho Yonghee said the team’s first playable versions received very harsh feedback from inside Capcom.\n\n“It was devastating,” “We were told that the game wasn’t interesting at all.”\n\nInstead of giving up, the team rebuilt big parts of the game.\n\nCho said, “Our failures guided us to success.”\n\nProducer Naoto Oyama added that the team kept improving the game through playtesting and feedback until they found the right balance between shooting, hacking, and exploration.",
    "author": 1,
    "date": "2026-06-30T14:24:57.028Z",
    "likes": []
  }
},
{
  "model": "network.post",
  "pk": 68,
  "fields": {
    "content": "The PlayStation post about the end of physical media has been Community Noted.\n\nIt has also received nearly 70,000 replies, with people extremely mad about it. This could be one of the Playstationbiggest backlash in recent years.\n\nPlayStation has also stopped posting since announcing the change.\n\n“Digital purchases grant a revocable license to access content, not ownership. Sony recently removed hundreds of purchased StudioCanal movies from libraries due to licensing.”\n",
    "author": 2,
    "date": "2026-07-03T12:47:06.030Z",
    "likes": [
      2
    ]
  }
},
